# Docs Discipline

- Always refer to relevant files in the `docs/` directory before making changes, except for small insignificant or UI-only tweaks
- Add or update a `docs/` file only when a change affects behavior, data models, system flows, or tRPC endpoints
- Use a docs-first checklist for non-trivial changes: read existing docs, update docs with behavior changes, then implement
- When modifying Prisma schema, update `docs/` to reflect data model and relationship changes
- When adding or modifying tRPC procedures, update the relevant `docs/` entries with new endpoints and behavior
